description:
One of my faves&#8230;....

	Vintage emerald green changeable satin brocade dress has an embossed look to it&#8217;s fabric surface, with black designs of flowers and vines. Almost a pebbly effect. Lovely!

	Dress has a full skirt , beautiful over a stiff slip or alone.
Metal side Talon zipper.

	The bodice is a little long for my short waisted dress form, it has a squared neckline, gathered to a modified sweetheart point. Sleeveless, with figure flattering Princess seaming on the bodice.

	The finishing touch is tiny glass prongset rhinestones scattered on the front, as well as glass rhinestone flowers.

	Seams are not serged or pinked.

	the only <span class="caps">MINOR</span> flaw on this beauty is that some of the rhinestone flowers have lost a little bit of their flash&#8230;..but still a very well preserved early 50&#8217;s dress!

